Being single is often associated with misery. But what if being alone doesn’t have to be dull and depressing?  Single people often get asked, “you don’t want to end up alone, do you?”, “how hasn’t anyone grabbed you up?” and “what’s wrong with you that you haven’t found anyone yet?” This then leads single people to start doubting themselves and thinking things like:  A single person might enter a relationship with the wrong person, so they do not feel alone. This can cause toxicity in the relationship and the person not actually wanting to be with their significant other.  It is very possible to be happy being single.  Here are some tips for being happy single:  Remember it is okay to be single – or in a relationship – there is no one size fits all! Sometimes people in relationships are also unhappy, and it is better to be single than to be in a miserable relationship.  There are happy singles and happy couples; you have to make sure that whatever choice you make that you are making that choice because you will be happier and healthier in the long run.